article.headline: 13-2 fourth-quarter run propels Atlanta
article.linkText: Hawks beat Nuggets for seventh straight time
article.story:
DENVER (AP) -- Stephen Jackson keyed a fourth-quarter run and scored a season-high 25 points to lead the Atlanta Hawks to their seventh straight victory over the Denver Nuggets, 84-76 Saturday night. Jackson scored seven points in a 13-2 run that gave Atlanta an 84-76 lead. Shareef Abdur-Rahim added 17 points for Atlanta, which hasn't lost to the Nuggets since Feb. 24, 2001. The win was only the third for the Hawks in their last 13 games. Carmelo Anthony led Denver with 26 points. The Nuggets managed only eight points in the fourth quarter and lost for just the fifth time at home. Earl Boykins hit two jumpers to put the Nuggets ahead 72-71 early in the fourth quarter, but Glover's two baskets and a jump shot by Jackson the Hawks a 79-72 lead. Marcus Camby ended the run with dunk with 5:16 remaining, but Denver went scoreless on its next seven possessions and Atlanta pulled away as Jackson tipped in a miss by Abdur-Rahim and then buried a 3-pointer with 3:03 left to make it 84-74. Anthony had four points as Denver opened the third quarter with a 6-0 run to move ahead 48-45, but Abdur-Rahim scored six points in an 8-0 run as the Hawks regained the lead, 53-48. Glover's free throw enabled Atlanta to take a 69-68 lead into the fourth quarter. The Hawks were up 20-16 after one quarter as Jackson had six points and Theo Ratliff blocked two shots. Anthony closed Denver to 34-32 with a pair of free throws and a short jumper and Andre Miller tied it at 36 with a baseline jumper. The game was tied two more times before Jackson's 3-pointer put Atlanta ahead 45-42 at halftime. Game notes
Atlanta played its third game in a six-game road trip. ... Ratliff has blocked a shot in 26 consecutive games. ... The Hawks are 5-15 on the road and have been outscored in the second quarter of six straight games. ... Anthony has reached double figures in all but two games for the Nuggets. ... The Nuggets lost to Atlanta 112-98 on Dec. 9 in Atlanta. ... Denver is 6-6 on the second night of back-back games.
